queen.} Qc7 (18... Qxc2 19. Qf7+ Kh8 20. Nxh7 $1 $18) 19. Nxh7 $18 {and the
attack was to much for Black in Ivanisevic,I (2646)-Onischuk,V (2628)
Zalakaros 2016}) 8. Bc4 Nb6 (8... Be6 {[%csl Yd5] is another option, trying to
establish blockade on the d5-point.} 9. Bxd5 Bxd5 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Qe2 $1 {
[%cal Yc2c4] The main goal of the f4 variation is to get the initiative or at
least a solid space advantage as soon as possible, so you should realize that
in each variation there is a different way towards this goal. Here White aims
to push the pawn to c4 and obtain a comfortable space advantage.} b5 {the
