knight vacates his initial developing square to make the consolidating move c3
possible. Besides, from e4 the knight has a plenty of good squares to go to
for either ofensive and defensive purposes, depending on what Black plays.} (
10. O-O {allows exchanges, although still White keeps a slight edge:} Nc6 11.
Be3 Na5 {eliminating the annoying bishop that prevents the central break f6})
10... Nc6 (10... Na6 11. Neg5 $1 {[%cal Gg5f7] with a dangerous threat Nxf7!}
