14. h4 $1 {By transposition, we have actually reached a position that was
played two times. This advance is really strong for White as Black has no
active ideas in the center and is still underdeveloped. Thus, this looks like
an appropriate moment to take the initiative.} N8e7 (14... h5 {[%csl Yg5]
eaving the g5-square unprotected is a high price to pay to stop white's pawn
advance.} 15. Bg5 N8e7 16. c3 Qd7 17. Ng3 $16 {[%csl Gf6][%cal Yg3e4] Black's
position looks just so cramped that soon he went for a piece sacrifice to get
some active play, but it was not enough in Popovic,D (2568)-Kegels,P (2120)
Gent Taminco 2013}) 15. h5 {White is not only getting rid of his only
potential weakness, but also opening an important file to attack the
opponent's king.} Nf5 16. c3 Re8 $2 (16... Qd7 17. Bc2 Nce7 {[%cal Ya8d8] was
