White has many strong attacking ideas, and probably Black's best chance is to
sacrifice a piece to slow down the attack.} Nxg4 (21... gxf5 22. Bxh6+ Rxh6 23.
gxf5 {is much better for White}) 22. f6+ (22. fxg6 $2 {now is bad due to} Ndxe5
$1 {revealling the detail behind 19...dxc4}) 22... Ngxf6 23. exf6+ Bxf6 {
Black managed to avoid the worst by sacrificing a piece. Still, after} 24. Ng3
$16 {White should be winning with accurate play.} *

