{A typical position that arises if Black plays ...d5. What should be White's
plan in this case and how to start?} 12. Nd1 $1 $16 {[%cal Gc2c3,Gg2g4,Gf4f5,
Yb3c2,Yd1e3] With the centre closed, White can think about a flank attack, and
thus turn his attention to the kingside. The plan is to solidify the center
with c3 and improve the pieces with Bc2 and Ne3. Later on, the f5 break
becomes thematic, with or without the help of g2-g4. Despite the apparent
slowness of this plan, it is difficult to see what Black can do to stop it.} *

