{Find a move that creates an unpleasant problem for Black in this position.} 
11. f5 $1 {[%csl Yg7] Not only is the Bg7 out of play now, but Black's pawn
structure on the kingside will become terribly damaged.} Nxf5 12. Bxf5 gxf5 13.
O-O Qb6 14. Ne2 Nd7 {with the simple c3 followed by Ng3xf5 White has a good
advantage, but also} 15. Be3 $5 Qxb2 16. Ng3 $1 {[%cal Yg3f5,Yf3g4] gave White
nice attacking prospects.} *

